events.name: Firebase Study Jam with Alex Astrum @Google Firebase Team - Firebase Extensions
events.description:
Hello GDG Cloud friends,

Alex Astrum @Google Firebase Team will join our Firebase Study Jam Online

Alex is a Software Engineer with 10+ years of web/mobile development experience.
Currently focused on Firebase, Angular & GCP.
Outside work, he loves games, outdoors & music.

You will have a chance to ask Alex questions via chat!
Codelab: Streamline application development with Firebase Extensions.
This is an online event. You will be able to access the link after you RSVP.

You will be able to access the link after you RSVP.

Join our community of like-minded developers and explore the latest Google Cloud technologies as a team.

We will use our Online Codelab "Streamline application development with Firebase Extensions" to build a web app from scratch with Firebase and Stackblitz's online editor. You will learn how to add new functionality to your app quickly with the latest Firebase features. We will use Firebase Extensions to make a web app more fully featured, with happier users. This is a great intro to using the Firebase console and integrating Firebase into an app. No extensive prior knowledge or software installations needed.

You will use the google.dev (https://google.dev/topics/firebase) platform. Google.dev is optional and allows attendees to create a developer profile and save their progress within a codelab. If you have used google.dev before, great! Make sure you know your password. If you haven‚Äôt, save time by creating a new Google.dev account for yourself prior to the workshop day (creating an account is free).

Agenda:
- Alex Astrum - Firebase Presentation + Q&A
- Codelab: Using Stackblitz‚Äôs online editor and Firebase Extensions to make a web app fully featured, with happier users.
